==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blotter
<hw>Blot"ter</hw> <pr>(bl⟦ocr⟧t"t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, blots; esp. a device for
absorbing superfluous ink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 158 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>A wastebook, in which entries of
transactions are made as they take place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blottesque</ent>⟦br⟧
